										<tr>
											<td width="100%" valign="top">					
												<!-- START NEWS AREAS-->
												<table width="90%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> FIERY DEFENDER</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'>To begin the Fiery Defender quest, one must first speak to Reklon Gnallen in the
Temple of Quellious within Erudin. Reklon gives you the basic information
regarding this quest, as well as the background information. The actual quest
giver is located within the Plane of Fear, a Fetid Fiend Irak Altil. After
asking 'why are you moaning?' Irak will explain that he was betrayed by a
corruptor of thought and stripped of all his holy arms. Asking you to cleanse
them he details the three items needed to be cleansed as well as where they can
be found:

<p><blockquote>You say, 'what sword?' 
<br><b>Irak Altil says 'Hands of a twisted brother no longer living.</b>

<p>You say, 'what shield' 
<b><br>Irak Altil says 'Earthly children of the god of hate. Keeping stand over his dark brothers and sisters.</b>

<p>You say, 'what breastplate' 
<b><br>Irak Altil lets loose an unearthly howl as it gleams with sickly light. 'Upon she who lured me from my post. In that place where hatred festers. Painful corruption.'</b></blockquote>

<p>The sword is found off the Keeper of Tombs, located within the hole. Spawn time is 7-10 days.
<br>The cleansing agent for the sword is a bucket of pure water, aquired from a mini-quest within Freeport. First say to the peasant woman found by the canal in West Freeport "What water?" She will hand you a bucket to take to her brother Joshua in the building beside her. Hand this to Joshua and you will recieve a bucket of pure water. Hand this and the sword to Reklon in Erudin to recieve the cleansed sword.
<p>The shield can be found off Kirik Vil, a level 55 guard in Nektulos Forest. Kirik has an extremely high regeneration rate and can be very tough. Spawn time is 7-10 days.
<br>There is no actual item as the cleansing agent for the shield. Instead go to Felwithe and hand this to Elia the Pure. She will hand you back the cleansed shield.
<p>The breastplate can be found off the Thought Destroyer in the Plane of Hate. This spawn is triggered randomly by killing various mobs within hate.
<br>To cleanse the breastplate one must complete a mini-quest located in Kaladim. Within the mines is an NPC named Jark. Hail him and say 'some'. Then proceed with the dialogue ending with the word 'dinner'. Go to Nella, who can be found next to the crystal pond in front of the Cleric guild. Hail her and say 'dinner' then give the dinner to Jark. You will recieve a pure crystal. Hand this and the breastplate to Reklon in Erudin to recieve the cleansed breastplate.

<p>Now finally hand all three cleansed items to Reklon in Erudin and he will state this dialogue:
<p><b><blockquote>Reklon Gnallen says 'I never thought our order would see these artifacts again. With the return of these relics we can now put at ease a scar upon the history of our order. This cleansing will atone for his failure. Your soul must be pure to have given so freely of yourself. Go now, take this crested token of our order. If you wish to free his soul you must undertake another sacrifice.</b>

<p>You say, 'what sacrifice'
<p><b>Reklon Gnallen says 'Only this crest and the sacrifice of something that symbolizes your strength and purity will release his spirit into the cleansing flames of our lady Quellious. Go now. Thank you Soandso.</b></blockquote>

<p>The crest he speaks of is the Mark of Atonement recieved by turning in all three cleansed items. This symbol of strength and purity is the Fiery Avenger. Take both these items to the Plane of Fear and hand them to Irak Atil. He will give you back the famed Fiery Defender.</td>
</tr>
